  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Everything we add to the library, be it JavaScript option or a cssClass in the default templates is an API addition. Once it's there, we cannot remove it. And we have to document it.\n\nSince the need was only expressed on one demo, I don't see the value of adding another API entry to hide the pagination, really no trying to dismiss the work you did. Just it doesn't seem to be that of a need that we need a new API entry.\n",
