    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I gave 7 lines of JS that solves this (hiding the widget).\n\nIf we keep adding options like that this has no end.\n\nProblem: when there's a single page I want to hide the pagination widget\nSolution: add a new css class with the pages count\n\nProblem: when the user selects a specific facet value I want to hide the refinement list\nSolution: add a new css class made of the facet value name currently selected\n\nThis do not scale. The particular use case we faced does not need to be adressed with a new API entry, we need to stop adding options like that.\n\nWhat we are doing here is take data from the results.\\* and put it as API entries inside the markup through html structure (here, css classes). There's no added value from taking all the results.\\* data and putting it everywhere in the API markup level.\n\nI won't add that just because it's easy to add and we can.\n",
